========================================
Test 1: CXL Type2 Snoop State Transitions
========================================
Protocol State Machine (MESI-like):

1. Read Request (I→S transition)
   CPU: Read miss, send SnpCur
   GPU: Snoop response with current state
   Coherency: Shared read allowed
   Latency: 279 ns
2. Write Request (S→M transition)
   CPU: Write hit, send SnpOwn (snoop invalidate)
   GPU: Must downgrade to Invalid
   Coherency: Exclusive write
   Latency: 126 ns
3. GPU Read During CPU Modify (M→S)
   GPU: Snoop request for data
   CPU: Downgrade to Shared, snoop response with data
   Coherency: Both can read
   Latency: 225 ns

State transition summary:
  Invalid→Shared:   Read-only path
  Shared→Modified:  Snoop invalidation required
  Modified→Shared:  Snoop data response required

